00:13:03,220 --> 00:13:04,470
Is something the matter?

251
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:06,220
What do you think is the matter?!

252
00:13:06,640 --> 00:13:08,930
She's Psiren! Look!

253
00:13:09,420 --> 00:13:12,120
The transmutation circle on her chest is more proof than anything!

254
00:13:13,450 --> 00:13:15,980
A lot can happen in one's life.

255
00:13:15,980 --> 00:13:18,990
You kids probably 
wouldn't understand.

256
00:13:18,990 --> 00:13:20,080
What?!

257
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:21,200
I understand.

258
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:27,110
I heard earlier that the hospital is going to be demolished.

259
00:13:27,110 --> 00:13:31,850
Clara-san, you had no choice but to become a thief in order to save the hospital, right?

260
00:13:31,850 --> 00:13:34,050
That's it, right, Clara-san?

261
00:13:35,340 --> 00:13:36,920
Th-That's right.

262
00:13:37,770 --> 00:13:41,260
I didn't want to become a thief.

263
00:13:41,260 --> 00:13:43,670
But in order to save 
the patients here,

264
00:13:43,670 --> 00:13:45,030
I had no choice.

265
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:48,000
I knew it.

266
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:49,800
You're such a kind person.

267
00:13:51,230 --> 00:13:52,250
Sensei!

268
00:13:52,250 --> 00:13:55,170
Sensei! There's another notice from Psiren...

269
00:13:56,240 --> 00:13:57,640
Is something the matter?

270
00:13:58,070 --> 00:13:59,000
Sensei?

271
00:14:01,450 --> 00:14:04,190
It looks like there's less security around this time.

272
00:14:04,190 --> 00:14:08,660
Yeah. The owner of this mansion is a very cautious man, you see.

273
00:14:08,930 --> 00:14:12,160
There's a little trap 
set up inside the mansion.

274
00:14:12,460 --> 00:14:13,370
A trap?

275
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:17,980
Just watch, and you'll understand. 
This time, Psiren has had it for sure!

276
00:14:17,980 --> 00:14:22,070
But the unexpected could always happen. If it does, we'll be counting on you.

277
00:14:24,530 --> 00:14:26,650
What should we do, Brother?

278
00:14:48,320 --> 00:14:50,020
Oh, no!

279
00:14:50,020 --> 00:14:51,020
A trap?

280
00:15:04,810 --> 00:15:06,250
Kid...

281
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:09,250
Why did you help me out?

282
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:11,610
I didn't particularly help <i>you</i> out.

283
00:15:11,610 --> 00:15:13,810
There are times when 
wrongdoing may be necessary.

284
00:15:13,810 --> 00:15:14,970
That's all I thought.

285
00:15:15,650 --> 00:15:17,830
If that's what it takes 
to save the hospital...

286
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:19,980
What's so funny?!

287
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:24,220
It's just that you sound like such a grown-up.

288
00:15:24,220 --> 00:15:25,730
I <i>am</i> a grown-up!

289
00:15:26,680 --> 00:15:31,240
Right. As a grown woman, 
I have to repay my debt to you.

290
00:15:31,880 --> 00:15:34,740
Is there anything you'd like me to do for you?

291
00:15:36,180 --> 00:15:37,950
Just answer me one thing.

292
00:15:38,330 --> 00:15:41,960
If you're an alchemist, you must've 
heard about the Philosopher's Stone.

293
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:44,880
If you have any information about it, tell me.

294
00:15:44,880 --> 00:15:47,460
I have to get that stone, 
no matter what.

295
00:15:50,110 --> 00:15:50,970
Sorry.

296
00:15:51,260 --> 00:15:53,440
It doesn't look like I can help you.

297
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:54,640
How about instead,

298
00:15:54,980 --> 00:15:58,890
if you ever find out where the stone is, you let me know? I'll steal it for you.

299
00:16:03,100 --> 00:16:04,400
Hey!

300
00:16:05,760 --> 00:16:08,150
I'm glad you're able 
to save the hospital.

301
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:11,490
Sure! Thanks to you!

302
00:16:16,140 --> 00:16:18,510
What's going on here?

303
00:16:18,510 --> 00:16:20,820
Don't tell me she tricked us...

304
00:16:20,820 --> 00:16:23,960
No way! Clara-san would be 
the last person to do something like that.

305
00:16:24,240 --> 00:16:25,870
There has to be 
some kind of mistake!

306
00:16:25,870 --> 00:16:28,440
The only mistakes going on are inside that head of yours!

307
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:31,010
<i>Clara</i> has robbed 
your head of <i>clarity</i>!

308
00:16:31,010 --> 00:16:33,320
That's terrible, Brother, 
saying it like that!

309
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:36,670
You mustn't argue. 
It goes against the will of God.

310
00:16:40,640 --> 00:16:42,180
Clara-san...

311
00:16:42,180 --> 00:16:43,600
You...?

312
00:16:44,830 --> 00:16:47,190
It's too bad about the hospital.

313
00:16:47,190 --> 00:16:51,360
I tried to save it, 
but I was too late.

314
00:16:51,360 --> 00:16:53,820
I was so beside myself 
with grief that I...

315
00:16:54,190 --> 00:16:55,530
became a nun!

316
00:16:55,530 --> 00:16:56,790
Clara-san!

317
00:16:56,790 --> 00:16:58,030
I'll just bet.

318
00:16:58,030 --> 00:16:59,810
It's true!

319
00:16:59,810 --> 00:17:01,730
Those who believe will be saved.

320
00:17:01,730 --> 00:17:05,400
And there are still others 
whom I can save.

321
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:07,040
For example, this convent.

322
00:17:07,290 --> 00:17:09,880
It will soon be demolished!

323
00:17:09,880 --> 00:17:11,590
I-I knew it!

324
00:17:11,590 --> 00:17:14,590
You're right! This time, 
you've got to stick with it, please!

325
00:17:14,590 --> 00:17:16,900
We'll give you our support, too!

326
00:17:18,940 --> 00:17:20,350
Brother! Bad news!

327
00:17:20,350 --> 00:17:21,640
What is it?!

328
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:24,640
They're saying that Psiren appeared again! 
The whole city is in an uproar!

329
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:28,100
She's done it! 
Now the convent can be saved!

330
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,070
There's some kind of mistake.

331
00:17:35,070 --> 00:17:36,620
Right, Brother?

332
00:17:36,620 --> 00:17:40,900
What are you, an idiot?! Quit being such a nice guy already! She's a con artist!

333
00:17:40,900 --> 00:17:42,880
She's just been teasing us 
and having herself a laugh!

334
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:45,100
Don't say it like that, Brother!

335
00:17:45,100 --> 00:17:48,250
You shouldn't fight. 
Stop it, boys.

336
00:17:51,800 --> 00:17:54,640
Why, you! What are you this time, in that getup?

337
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:57,610
I know! You've become a schoolteacher, right?

338
00:17:57,610 --> 00:18:00,720
You're fighting for a school 
that's soon to be destroyed!

339
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:03,470
That's it, right? 
Isn't that right, Clara-san?!

340
00:18:03,980 --> 00:18:07,200
Y-Yes, yes. Well done.

341
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:08,190
Stop jerking us around!

342
00:18:08,930 --> 00:18:12,690
What are you? 
Are you just a thief after all?

343
00:18:12,690 --> 00:18:16,950
A common criminal, who uses alchemy for her own selfish interests?!

344
00:18:18,870 --> 00:18:20,450
Well, that's a good question.

345
00:18:21,060 --> 00:18:22,950
You're a grown-up, right?

346
00:18:23,580 --> 00:18:25,450
Think about it for yourself.

347
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:34,050
Extra! Extra!

348
00:18:34,430 --> 00:18:37,050
Another notice from Psiren!

349
00:18:37,480 --> 00:18:41,660
What are you so pleased about? 
Psiren is just a common criminal, right?

350
00:18:41,660 --> 00:18:46,140
What are you talking about? We owe Psiren for saving the city of Aquroya.

351
00:18:46,140 --> 00:18:48,750
She's our star of hope, you know!

352
00:18:48,750 --> 00:18:50,650
Your star of hope?

353
00:18:51,390 --> 00:18:54,000
This city—the City of Water, Aquroya—

354
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:57,150
sinks a little bit into 
the water every year.

355
00:18:57,150 --> 00:19:01,660
In another five years, the whole city will be wiped out at the bottom of the lake.

356
00:19:01,660 --> 00:19:05,300
Because of that, 
everyone else fled the city.

357
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:10,420
That made us all so lonesome. At least until Psiren appeared.

358
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:15,130
But thanks to Psiren, 
life has returned to the city.

359
00:19:15,130 --> 00:19:17,170
Reporters from all over the country 
and tourists alike

360
00:19:17,170 --> 00:19:20,510
come here in the hope of 
catching a glimpse of Psiren.

361
00:19:20,510 --> 00:19:22,540
Before disappearing under the water,

362
00:19:22,540 --> 00:19:26,180
she has made Aquroya bloom one last time.

363
00:19:27,470 --> 00:19:29,990
What does it mean, Brother?

364
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:35,100
Could it be that Clara-san 
became a thief to save the city?

365
00:19:35,100 --> 00:19:38,190
Maybe. The one thing 
I can say for sure...

366
00:19:38,190 --> 00:19:40,950
is that she tricked me—

367
00:19:41,330 --> 00:19:43,320
the Fullmetal Alchemist.

368
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:47,350
She's going to pay for that offense, at least.

369
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:00,670
I thought you would come,

370
00:20:01,030 --> 00:20:01,970
kid.

371
00:20:03,010 --> 00:20:06,700
Pretty fantastic, isn't it? 
A date here, on the water.

372
00:20:06,700 --> 00:20:08,830
Shut up, you crook.

373
00:20:08,830 --> 00:20:11,700
Dear me, the same could be said of you, couldn't it?

374
00:20:11,700 --> 00:20:14,020
You want the Philosopher's Stone, right?

375
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:16,520
The desire to have an object...

376
00:20:17,070 --> 00:20:18,690
is the same in both of us.

377
00:20:19,410 --> 00:20:20,480
Maybe so.

378
00:20:20,990 --> 00:20:21,650
However...

379
00:20:21,910 --> 00:20:23,900
there is something that's different.

380
00:20:23,900 --> 00:20:28,160
What we use our alchemy for, 
and the burdens we each bear.

381
00:20:29,720 --> 00:20:31,410
Here I go, kid.

382
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:40,830
I did it...

383
00:21:06,780 --> 00:21:09,080
That was pretty sharp, kid.

384
00:21:09,080 --> 00:21:13,610
I'm sure you'll turn into a fine man. 
Once you do, let's fight again.

385
00:21:13,610 --> 00:21:16,180
Next time, as a man and a woman.

386
00:21:16,180 --> 00:21:17,910
Clara-san...

387
00:21:17,910 --> 00:21:20,750
Let me tell you one last thing.

388
00:21:21,120 --> 00:21:22,500
It's about the Philosopher's Stone.

389
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:23,340
What?

390
00:21:23,750 --> 00:21:26,480
Go to the city of Xenotime and have a look.

391
00:21:26,480 --> 00:21:31,270
I've heard that there's somebody there researching the Philosopher's Stone.

392
00:21:32,410 --> 00:21:33,670
Xenotime...

393
00:21:37,350 --> 00:21:41,640
What, are you still angry? 
I had no choice, you know.

394
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:44,490
She was, after all, 
a common criminal.

395
00:21:44,490 --> 00:21:45,450
She was <i>not</i>!

396
00:21:46,390 --> 00:21:48,870
She wasn't just 
a common criminal.

397
00:21:48,870 --> 00:21:52,770
Brother, you said yourself that sometimes, wrongdoing is necessary, didn't you?

398
00:21:53,500 --> 00:21:54,850
Clara-san was...

399
00:21:55,460 --> 00:21:58,550
Clara-san was a kind person.

400
00:21:58,550 --> 00:22:00,960
You really think so too, Brother!

401
00:22:03,320 --> 00:22:04,670
About that...

402
00:22:05,640 --> 00:22:07,980
I'm not sure.

403
00:22:12,990 --> 00:22:15,480
Say, it's a little bit warm in here.

404
00:22:16,150 --> 00:22:18,980
Could I get you to lower the zipper on my chest?

405
00:22:29,990 --> 00:22:35,700
With you always in my sight, I can manage to draw breath

406
00:22:29,990 --> 00:22:35,700
itsumo no shisen ni kimi ga ite kokyuu ga dekiru

407
00:22:35,700 --> 00:22:43,100
And for me, that ought to be enough in itself, and yet...

408
00:22:35,700 --> 00:22:43,100
boku ni totte nara sore dake de mou juubun na hazu na no ni

409
00:22:44,850 --> 00:22:51,000
All little old me ever does is repeat the same old mistakes

410
00:22:44,850 --> 00:22:51,000
chippoke na boku wa kurikaesu ayamachi bakari

411
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:54,460
How much strength do I need to come by

412
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:54,460
dore hodo tsuyosa wo te ni shitara

413
00:22:54,460 --> 00:22:58,430
before I can get by without hurting anything?

414
00:22:54,460 --> 00:22:58,430
nanimo kizutsukezu ni sumu no?

415
00:22:58,800 --> 00:23:01,960
I am not going to stray, I'm going to trust this love,

416
00:22:58,800 --> 00:23:01,960
mayowazu ni kono ai wo,

417
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:04,770
and with it I will go on living!

418
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:04,770
shinjikite yuku

419
00:23:04,770 --> 00:23:06,330
I'm going to take these wounds,

420
00:23:04,770 --> 00:23:06,330
fusagaranu

421
00:23:06,330 --> 00:23:11,020
the ones that will not close, and squeeze them tight!

422
00:23:06,330 --> 00:23:11,020
kizuguchi mo gyutto dakishimete

423
00:23:11,020 --> 00:23:11,280
The two of us must keep on walking,

424
